Brighton manager, Graham Potter, has praised three Chelsea players ahead of his side’s Premier League clash against Frank Lampard’s men at Stamford Bridge on Saturday. Potter hailed the quality of Tammy Abraham, Fikayo Tomori and Mason Mount and said he came across them in the Championship last season. Potter’s men head to the game following a goalless draw with Newcastle United in the Premier League last weekend. Speaking to reporters at his pre-match press conference ahead Saturday’s clash, Potter said: ”Chelsea have some really good young players – I came across them in the Championship last season. “We knew the likes of Abraham, Mount and Tomori would do well. Frank Lampard knows them well too, which always helps.” The kick-off time for the match is 3pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.